221500%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EJamie%20Dimon.%3Cp%3EBrian%20Snyder%2FReuters%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EJamie%20Dimon%20sees%20far%20greater%20threats%20than%20recession%2C%20and%20the%20potential%20for%20more%20banking%20turmoil.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EThe%20JPMorgan%20CEO%20is%20skeptical%20of%20the%20work-from-home%20trend%2C%20and%20says%20America%20shouldn't%20fear%20China.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EHere%20are%20Dimon's%2012%20best%20quotes%20from%20a%20new%20interview.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EJamie%20Dimon%20flagged%20the%20risk%20of%20further%20banking%20turmoil%2C%20warned%20there%20are%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fjpmorgan-jamie-dimon-consumer-spending-economy-recession-inflation-war-food-2023-7%5C%22%3Emuch%20graver%20threats%20today%3C%2Fa%3E%20than%20a%20possible%20US%20recession%2C%20and%20urged%20America%20not%20to%20be%20cowed%20by%20China%2C%20in%20an%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.youtube.com%2Fwatch%3Fv%3DBU76qx8Xpcw%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Einterview%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%20The%20Economist%20released%20this%20week.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJPMorgan's%20billionaire%20CEO%20also%20pushed%20back%20against%20rumours%20he%20might%20run%20for%20president%2C%20cast%20doubt%20on%20the%20working-from-home%20boom%2C%20and%20shared%20what%20he'd%20like%20his%20legacy%20to%20be.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EHere%20are%20Dimon's%2012%20best%20quotes%2C%20lightly%20edited%20for%20length%20and%20clarity%3A%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E1.%20%26quot%3BWe%20all%20want%20to%20be%20in%20a%20position%20where%20banks%20can%20fail%20and%20the%20world%20doesn't%20go%20down%20the%20tubes.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E2.%20%26quot%3BThere%20was%20a%20problem%20in%20plain%20sight%2C%20which%20was%20some%20interest-rate%20exposure%2C%20some%20of%20these%20uninsured%20deposits%20that%20ran%20like%20a%20flock%20of%20birds.%20It's%20over%20for%20now%2C%20most%20of%20it's%20been%20handled.%20If%20rates%20go%20up%20from%20here%2C%20and%20they%20might%2C%20it%20could%20rear%20its%20ugly%20head%20again.%26quot%3B%20(Dimon%20was%20discussing%20the%20banking%20chaos%20sparked%20by%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsilicon-valley-bank-failure-what-happened-bank-run-explained-2023-3%5C%22%3ESilicon%20Valley%20Bank's%20collapse%3C%2Fa%3E%20earlier%20this%20year.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E3.%20%26quot%3BConsumers%20have%20money%2C%20they%20have%20%241%20trillion%20more%20in%20their%20checking%20accounts.%20It's%20been%20coming%20down%2C%20and%20we%20think%20sometime%20around%20the%20end%20of%20the%20year%20that%20excess%20money%20will%20be%20spent.%20Even%20if%20we%20go%20into%20recession%2C%20consumer's%20in%20great%20shape%2C%20businesses%20are%20in%20pretty%20good%20shape.%26quot%3B%20(Dimon%20noted%20that%20many%20Americans%20have%20benefited%20from%20wage%20growth%20and%20more%20than%20a%20decade%20of%20rising%20stock%20prices%20and%20home%20values.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E4.%20%26quot%3BI'm%20much%20more%20worried%20about%20some%20of%20these%20other%20serious%20things%20getting%20worse%3A%20the%20war%20in%20Ukraine%20spreading%20out%2C%20nuclear%20blackmail%3B%20if%20food%20doesn't%20get%20delivered%2C%20starvation%20in%20Africa.%20All%20these%20things%20may%20mitigate%20and%20go%20away%2C%20and%20we'll%20all%20breathe%20a%20deep%20sigh%20of%20relief.%20I%20wouldn't%20count%20on%20that.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E5.%20%26quot%3BI%20can't%20get%20past%20the%20notion%20that%20we've%20never%20had%20it%20before.%20We've%20never%20had%20quantitative%20easing%20like%20this%20before%2C%20we've%20never%20had%20quantitative%20tightening%20before.%20I%20think%20the%20effects%20on%20that%20in%20the%20market%20may%20be%20more%20serious%20than%20other%20people%20think.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E6.%20%26quot%3BWe've%20done%20a%20terrible%20job%20on%20immigration%2C%20taxation%2C%20mortgages%2C%20affordable%20housing%2C%20healthcare.%20Obesity%2C%20diabetes%20%E2%80%94%20teaching%20kids%20that%20at%20school.%26quot%3B%20(Dimon%20was%20laying%20out%20why%20the%20US%20economy%20has%20grown%20by%20less%20than%202%25%20a%20year%20over%20the%20last%20two%20decades%20or%20so%2C%20instead%20of%203%25.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E7.%20%26quot%3BWe%20should%20be%20looking%20at%20our%20own%20flaws%20and%20not%20always%20blaming%20other%20people.%20The%20Chinese%20are%20not%2010-feet%20tall.%20The%20notion%20that%20somehow%20America%20has%20to%20be%20that%20afraid%20of%20China%20%E2%80%94%20they%20don't.%26quot%3B%20(Dimon%20underscored%20China's%20reliance%20on%20food%20and%20oil%20imports%2C%20lower%20GDP%20per%20capita%2C%20and%20inferior%20military%20compared%20to%20the%20US.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E8.%20%26quot%3BI%20would%20worry%20about%20another%20Trump%20presidency%20too%20by%20the%20way.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E9.%20%26quot%3BI've%20never%20really%20believed%20I'm%20suited%20for%20it.%20I%20also%20think%20if%20you're%20going%20to%20do%20that%2C%20you%20should%20practice.%20You%20don't%20just%20say%2C%20'Oh%20I'm%20going%20to%20run%20for%20office.'%26quot%3B%20(Dimon%20was%20asked%20about%20his%20political%20ambitions.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E10.%20%26quot%3BIt%20doesn't%20work%20for%20younger%20kids%20in%20apprenticeships.%20It%20doesn't%20really%20work%20for%20creativity%20and%20spontaneity.%20It%20doesn't%20really%20work%20for%20management%20teams.%20There%20are%20real%20flaws.%20To%20the%20extent%20it%20works%2C%20I'm%20okay%20with%20it.%20If%20it%20doesn't%20work%2C%20I%20don't%20mind%20getting%20rid%20of%20it.%20We're%20not%20going%20to%20make%20that%20decision%20because%20we're%20pandering%20to%20employees%20%E2%80%94%20that%20is%20not%20the%20way%20to%20build%20a%20great%20company.%20So%20count%20me%20as%20a%20skeptic.%26quot%3B%20(Dimon%20was%20sharing%20his%20view%20on%20working%20from%20home.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E11.%20%26quot%3BI%20completely%20understand%20why%20someone%20doesn't%20want%20to%20commute%20an%20hour%20and%20a%20half%20every%20day%2C%20totally%20got%20it.%20Doesn't%20mean%20they%20have%20to%20have%20a%20job%20here%20either.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E12.%20%26quot%3BAll%20I%20ever%20cared%20about%20my%20legacy%20is%20that%20people%20say%20we're%20gonna%20miss%20the%20son%20of%20a%20bitch%2C%20and%20he%20made%20the%20world%20a%20better%20place%20while%20he%20was%20here.%20%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fjpmorgan-jamie-dimon-recession-banking-crisis-wfh-china-president-legacy-2023-7%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689254717000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F64afed49c22d1a00194540a9%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fjpmorgan-jamie-dimon-recession-banking-crisis-wfh-china-president-legacy-2023-7%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22JPMorgan%20CEO%20Jamie%20Dimon%20discusses%20recession%2C%20banking%20risks%2C%20working%20from%20home%2C%20global%20threats%2C%20US-China%20concerns%2C%20and%20his%20legacy%20in%20a%20new%20interview.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22tmohamed%40insider.com%20(Theron%20Mohamed)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A2%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fmarkets.businessinsider.com%2Fnews%2Fstocks%2Fjpmorgan-jamie-dimon-recession-banking-crisis-wfh-china-president-legacy-2023-7%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22First%20over-the-counter%20birth%20control%20pill%20gets%20FDA%20approval%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689254505000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-101732751%2Cimgsize-1638456.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Ffirst-over-the-counter-birth-control-pill-gets-fda-approval%2Farticleshow%2F101732538.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2F