20fail%20to%20make%20a%20perfect%20meal%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20laughs.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOften%2C%20her%20mother%20would%20come%20to%20her%20rescue.%20%E2%80%9CShe%20used%20to%20write%20letters%20to%20us%20from%20Kolkata.%20In%20those%20letters%2C%20she%20would%20write%20a%20recipe%20and%20cooking%20method%20for%20me%20in%20Urdu.%20During%20vacations%20when%20we%20would%20be%20home%2C%20I%20used%20to%20learn%20from%20her.%20The%20first%20thing%20I%20learnt%20from%20her%20was%20%3Cem%3Eshami%20kabab%3C%2Fem%3E.%20My%20father%20relished%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20getting%20married%2C%20Manzilat%20settled%20in%20Kolkata.%20She%20loved%20to%20host%20guests%20of%20her%20husband%20and%20friends%20of%20her%20children.%20Through%20cooking%20over%20the%20years%2C%20she%20developed%20an%20immense%20interest%20in%20food.%20%E2%80%9CBut%20I%20never%20knew%20that%20I%20would%20build%20a%20career%20in%20it%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20smiles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201200px)%20100vw%2C%201200px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fkolkata-biryani-1-1689173324.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Manzilat%20runs%20a%20home%20diner%20that%20keeps%20a%20number%20of%20royal%20delicacies%20alive.%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fkolkata-biryani-1-1689173324.jpg%201200w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fkolkata-biryani-1-1689173324-300x157.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fkolkata-biryani-1-1689173324-500x262.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fkolkata-biryani-1-1689173324-768x402.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fkolkata-biryani-1-1689173324-150x79.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-323617%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22628%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3EManzilat%20runs%20a%20home%20diner%20that%20keeps%20a%20number%20of%20royal%20delicacies%20alive.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20a%20bid%20to%20keep%20the%20legacy%20of%20royal%20delicacies%20alive%2C%20she%20set%20up%20Manzilat%E2%80%99s%20home%20diner%20in%20Kasba%20of%20Kolkata%20in%202018.%20%E2%80%9CAll%20the%20nawabs%20were%20very%20fond%20of%20food%20and%20Awadhi%20cuisine%20is%20very%20popular%20but%20not%20so%20popular%20outside%20Lucknow.%20People%20even%20in%20Lucknow%20and%20Metiabruz%20do%20not%20know%20the%20history%20associated%20with%20the%20food.%20I%20wanted%20to%20contribute%20towards%20carrying%20the%20legacy%20of%20my%20family%20before%20the%20world%20forgets%20our%20lineage%20and%20the%20relevance%20of%20food%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EManzilat%20manages%20her%20home%20diner%20with%20the%20help%20of%20four%20workers%20and%20caters%20to%20foodies%20from%20across%20the%20world%2C%20including%20Japan%2C%20China%2C%20Abu%20Dhabi%2C%20Toronto%2C%20New%20Jersey%2C%20and%20Singapore.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CMy%20mission%20is%20not%20to%20earn%20from%20a%20commercial%20set%20up%2C%20but%20to%20spread%20awareness%20on%20the%20history%20of%20Awadh%2C%20its%20last%20King%20Wajid%20Ali%20Shah%2C%20freedom%20fighter%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F156185%2Fbegum-hazrat-mahal-british-1857-mutiny%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBegum%20Hazrat%20Mahal%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20and%20our%20family%20history.%20For%20this%2C%20I%20get%20immense%20love%2C%20honour%2C%20and%20respect%2C%20which%20is%20priceless.%20That%20is%20my%20real%20earning%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EEdited%20by%20Divya%20Sethu%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1689227864000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F07%2Fkolkata-biryani-2-1689173481.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F%3Fp%3D323582%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20descendant%20of%20King%20Wajid%20Ali%20Shah%20and%20Begum%20Hazrat%20Mahal%2C%20Manzilat%20runs%20a%20home%20diner%20that%20keeps%20a%20number%20of%20royal%20delicacies%20alive%2C%20in%20particular%20the%20Kolkata%20Biryani%2C%20which%20she%20says%20has%20deep%20roots%20in%20the%20region%20of%20Lucknow.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22Shivani%20Gupta%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A6%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F323582%2Fmanzilat-descendant-of-wajid-ali-shah-keeps-family-history-of-kolkata-biryani-alive%2F%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22More%20Than%20100%20Ex%20Civil%20Servants%20Question%20New%20Forest%20Conservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2022%2F01%2F14144301%2F2_Forests_of_Sikkim_India_Mist__Trees.jpeg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ENew%20Delhi%3A%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3EMore%20than%20100%20former%20civil%20servants%2C%20members%20of%20the%20Constitutional%20Conduct%20Group%20(CCG)%2C%20have%20written%20to%20all%20members%20of%20parliament%20in%20India%20expressing%20their%20concern%20with%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023.%20The%20group%20has%20said%20they%20are%20worried%20both%20by%20the%20contents%20of%20the%20Bill%20and%20the%20process%20being%20followed%20in%20passing%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CProcedurally%2C%20the%20Bill%20should%20have%20been%20referred%20to%20the%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20on%20science%2C%20technology%2C%20environment%20and%20forests%2C%20instead%20of%20being%20referred%20to%20a%20Select%20Committee%2C%20all%20the%20members%20of%20which%2C%20except%20one%2C%20belong%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20making%20the%20examination%20partisan%20and%20unsatisfactory%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20letter%20states.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CBesides%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20overturn%20the%20praiseworthy%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20of%201996%20in%20the%20Godavarman%20case%20(which%2C%20inter%20alia%2C%20defined%20forests%20as%20any%20piece%20of%20land%20that%20resembles%20the%20dictionary%20meaning%20of%20forest)%2C%20one%20of%20its%20most%20damaging%20provisions%20is%20to%20allow%20forest%20lands%20within%20100%20kms.%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20borders%20to%20be%20used%20for%20%E2%80%98strategic%20linear%20projects%20of%20national%20importance%20and%20concerning%20national%20security%E2%80%99%2C%E2%80%9D%20it%20continues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERead%20the%20full%20text%20of%20the%20letter%20below.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%C2%A7%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHonourable%20MPs%20of%20the%20Lok%20Sabha%2C%3Cbr%3E%5CnHonourable%20MPs%20of%20the%20Rajya%20Sabha%2C%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20a%20group%20of%20former%20civil%20servants%20of%20the%20All%20India%20and%20Central%20Services%20who%20have%20worked%20with%20the%20Central%20and%20State%20Governments%20in%20the%20course%20of%20our%20careers.%20As%20a%20group%2C%20we%20have%20no%20affiliation%20with%20any%20political%20party%20but%20believe%20in%20impartiality%2C%20neutrality%20and%20commitment%20to%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWe%20are%20deeply%20perturbed%20by%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20(Amendment)%20Bill%2C%202023%2C%20which%20was%20introduced%20in%20Parliament%20in%20March%202023%20and%20is%20slated%20to%20be%20passed%20in%20the%20coming%20monsoon%20session.%C2%A0%20Our%20concerns%20are%20both%20about%20the%20content%20of%20the%20Bill%20as%20well%20as%20the%20procedure%20by%20which%20the%20Bill%20is%20being%20examined%20and%20passed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EProcedurally%2C%20the%20Bill%20should%20have%20been%20referred%20to%20the%20Parliamentary%20Committee%20on%20science%2C%20technology%2C%20environment%20and%20forests%2C%20instead%20of%20being%20referred%20to%20a%20Select%20Committee%2C%20all%20the%20members%20of%20which%2C%20except%20one%2C%20belong%20to%20the%20ruling%20party%2C%20making%20the%20examination%20partisan%20and%20unsatisfactory.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20historical%20reason%20for%20the%20passing%20of%20the%20Forest%20Conservation%20Act%20(FCA)%20in%201980%2C%20viz.%20to%20prevent%20deforestation%2C%20needs%20to%20be%20appreciated%2C%20before%20we%20discuss%20the%20present%20Bill.%20%C2%A0In%20the%20thirty%20years%20prior%20to%201980%2C%20about%204.2%20million%20hectares%20of%20forest%20land%20were%20lost%2C%20being%20diverted%20for%20non-forestry%20purposes.%20In%20over%20forty%20years%20since%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20FCA%2C%201980%2C%20only%20about%201.5%20million%20hectares%20have%20been%20diverted.%20Even%20though%20the%20adverse%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20were%20not%20obvious%20in%201980%2C%20it%20is%20a%20testament%20to%20the%20sagacity%20of%20our%20lawmakers%20that%20they%20considered%20it%20critical%20to%20regulate%20the%20diversion%20of%20forest%20lands%20through%20the%20enactment%20of%20the%20FCA%2C%201980.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnfortunately%2C%20in%20the%20last%20few%20years%2C%20despite%20the%20adverse%20impacts%20of%20climate%20change%20becoming%20increasingly%20obvious%20%E2%80%93%20the%20floods%20now%20sweeping%20north%20India%20are%20a%20glaring%20example%20%E2%80%93%20the%20diversion%20of%20forest%20lands%20has%20gathered%20pace.%C2%A0%20Between%202018-19%20and%202022-23%2C%20almost%2090%2C000%20hectares%20of%20forest%20land%20have%20been%20diverted%20for%20non-forest%20use.%20The%20institutions%20of%20the%20Forest%20Advisory%20Committee%20and%20the%20Regional%20Empowered%20Committees%2C%20which%20are%20meant%20to%20regulate%20and%20minimise%20this%20diversion%2C%20have%20been%20ineffective.%20Hardly%20any%20proposal%20for%20diversion%20of%20forest%20land%20seems%20to%20be%20rejected!%20In%202020%2C%20alone%2C%20of%20the%20367%20proposals%20received%20for%20diversion%20of%2014%2C855%20hectares%20of%20forest%20land%2C%20only%203%20proposals%20amounting%20to%20about%2011%20hectares%20were%20rejected!%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20tendency%20of%20liberally%20giving%20away%20forest%20land%20for%20non-forest%20purposes%2C%20is%20now%20sought%20to%20be%20further%20strengthened%20through%20the%20FCA%20Amendment%20Bill.%20This%20Bill%20allows%20forest%20land%2C%20other%20than%20in%20protected%20areas%2C%20to%20be%20used%20for%20several%20non-forest%20purposes%2C%20viz.%20(i)%20defence%20related%20purposes%20within%20100%20kms.%20of%20the%20border%20of%20India%3B%20(ii)%20stretches%20of%20land%20alongside%20railway%20lines%20and%20highways%3B%20(iii)%20zoos%20and%20safaris%C2%A0owned%20by%20the%20government%20or%20any%20authority%3B%20(iv)%20eco-tourism%20facilities%3B%20(v)%20silvicultural%20operations%20(to%20enhance%20forest%20growth)%3B%20and%2C%20most%20worryingly%2C%20(vi)%20any%20other%20purpose%20specified%20by%20the%20central%20government.%20The%20Bill%20also%20specifies%20that%20reconnaissance%20and%20prospecting%20surveys%2C%20among%20other%20surveying%20activities%2C%20may%20be%20undertaken%2C%20under%20conditions%20to%20be%20specified%20by%20the%20central%20government.%20One%20wonders%20what%20is%20the%20purpose%20of%20prospecting%20surveys%3F%20Does%20it%20mean%20that%20if%20any%20important%20minerals%20are%20found%20in%20dense%20forests%2C%20mining%20will%20be%20allowed%3F%20A%20recent%20print%20article%20mentions%20that%20diamond%20mining%20is%20proposed%20to%20be%20undertaken%20in%20the%20dense%20natural%20forests%20of%20Buxwaha%2C%20in%20Madhya%20Pradesh%2C%20even%20though%20this%20will%20endanger%20water%20availability%20in%20the%20region%2C%20and%20contribute%20to%20%C2%A0local%20as%20well%20as%20global%20warming.%20Permission%20for%20this%20mining%20project%20has%20been%20given%20even%20under%20the%20existing%2C%20stricter%2C%20Act.%20What%20will%20happen%20once%20the%20Act%20is%20amended%2C%20and%20permissions%20are%20granted%20freely%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20preamble%20of%20the%20Bill%20mentions%20that%20as%20a%20result%20of%20this%20Bill%2C%20forest%20and%20tree%20cover%20will%20be%20increased%20to%20create%20a%20carbon%20sink%20of%20an%20additional%202.5%20to%203.0%20billion%20tonnes%20of%20CO2%20equivalent%2C%20by%202030.%20It%20puts%20its%20faith%2C%20apparently%2C%20in%20compensatory%20afforestation.%20Such%20an%20expectation%20is%20unrealistic%20given%20the%20fact%20that%20large%20tracts%20of%20existing%20natural%20forests%20will%20be%20diverted%20for%20non-forest%20use.%20There%20are%20ample%20studies%20which%20suggest%20that%20natural%20forests%20are%20forty%20times%20more%20efficient%20as%20carbon%20sinks%20than%20newly%20planted%20forests.%20%C2%A0%C2%A0Moreover%2C%20the%20results%20of%20compensatory%20afforestation%2C%20as%20of%20today%2C%20have%20not%20been%20rosy.%20Between%202008%20and%202019%2C%20an%20area%20equal%20to%20only%2072%25%20of%20the%20diverted%20forest%20area%20was%20brought%20under%20compensatory%20afforestation%3B%20moreover%2C%2024%25%20of%20this%20was%20on%20existing%2C%20but%20degraded%2C%20forest%20land.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20important%20to%20remember%20that%20natural%20forests%20are%20important%20not%20only%20as%20carbon%20sinks%20but%20also%20because%20they%20harbour%20immensely%20precious%20flora%20and%20fauna.%20India%20is%20one%20of%20only%2017%20megadiverse%20countries%20in%20the%20world%20with%20more%20than%205000%20endemic%20species%20of%20plants%20and%20animals.%20This%20myopic%20Bill%20threatens%20all%20of%20this%20biodiversity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBesides%20the%20fact%20that%20the%20Bill%20seeks%20to%20overturn%20the%20praiseworthy%20Supreme%20Court%20judgment%20of%201996%20in%20the%20Godavarman%20case%20(which%2C%20inter%20alia%2C%20defined%20forests%20as%20any%20piece%20of%20land%20that%20resembles%20the%20dictionary%20meaning%20of%20forest)%2C%20one%20of%20its%20most%20damaging%20provisions%20is%20to%20allow%20forest%20lands%20within%20100%20kms.%20of%20the%20country%E2%80%99s%20borders%20to%20be%20used%20for%20%E2%80%98strategic%20linear%20projects%20of%20national%20importance%20and%20concerning%20national%20security%E2%80%99.%20This%20100%20km.%20stretch%20would%20cover%20all%20the%20north-eastern%20States%20and%20would%20include%20Sikkim%20and%20Uttarakhand%20%E2%80%93%20states%20which%20have%20the%20highest%20forest%20cover%20in%20the%20country%20and%20are%20also%20biodiversity%20hotspots.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20preamble%20of%20the%20Bill%20also%20mentions%20that%20it%20will%20%3Cem%3E%E2%80%9Cenhance%20forest%20based%20economic%2C%20social%20and%20environmental%20benefits%2C%20including%20improvement%20of%20livelihoods%20of%20forest%20dependent%20communities%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%C2%A0One%20of%20the%20main%20Acts%20which%20supports%20forest%20dependent%20communities%20is%20the%20Forest%20Rights%20Act%20(FRA)%202006.%20The%20current%20Bill%20does%20not%20contain%20any%20provision%20to%20protect%20the%20rights%20granted%20under%20the%20FRA%3B%20nor%20does%20it%20mention%20whether%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20Bill%20are%20in%20conflict%20or%20conformity%20with%20the%20provisions%20of%20the%20FRA.%20For%20example%2C%20what%20happens%20if%20the%20lands%2C%20on%20which%20one%20or%20more%20forest%20communities%20depend%2C%20are%20leased%20out%20for%20eco-tourism%20or%20safari%20parks%20or%20used%20for%20defence%20installations%3F%20This%20conflict%20was%20observed%20by%20Mr%20Harsh%20Chauhan%2C%20until%20recently%20the%20Chairman%20of%20the%20National%20Commission%20on%20Scheduled%20Tribes%3B%20he%20resigned%2C%20reportedly%2C%20because%20his%20request%20that%20the%20Bill%20be%20deferred%20was%20not%20accepted%20by%20the%20government.%20It%20is%20apparent%20that%20far%20from%20protecting%20forest%20dependent%20communities%2C%20the%20Bill%20may%20actually%20threaten%20their%20livelihoods%20and%20their%20lives.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArticle%2048A%20of%20the%20Constitution%20says%20that%